Hello Clara,



I am a evp-itc researcher and interested in the paranormal as you obviously
are. I created a program to simply put it.to acknowledge hard working people
who donate their lives, their blood, sweat and tears to opening doors to
learning to speak to the dead, ufo&#39;s and anything paranormal. I am also the
Moderator of this group. I do not normally send out invites , this is my
first as this is the first in History that I am completely aware of to help
people network, make friends, promote their work and ideas on this new site.
And to give the an award for their hard earned work!!  I hope that you will
go visit and watch the video and read what I have to say. If you don&#39;t like
it.then that&#39;s ok too. There are a lot of people here, that  I admire, that
are in the background and working  hard almost daily, I just want to show my
appreciation in ALL that ALL of YOU do!



Blessings,

Laura Kimberley

Director of IPAA



From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Clara Febach
Sent: Tuesday, December 02, 2008 12:50 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [SPAM]Re: [EVP-ITC] The IPAA Official Nominees Site is now OPEN!




Who is IPAA and why am I receiving this information with a link for me to
click on?



I would prefer not to receive these kinds of invitations through this group.
I usually get enough ads as it is without getting them enclosed in messages
from groups I belong to. In the past I have received invitations sent
directly to my email address and read them when it is convenient for me to
take EXTRA time to read them.



Please don&#39;t make me hesitate to open EVP-ITC messages.



Thank you.


--- On Tue, 12/2/08, ghuny1 &lt;itcnap@...&gt; wrote:

From: ghuny1 &lt;itcnap@...&gt;
Subject: [EVP-ITC] The IPAA Official Nominees Site is now OPEN!
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Date: Tuesday, December 2, 2008, 10:27 AM

Dear Friends,

Welcome to the Official IPAA Nominations site. This is a new venture
and has never been done before on this global level. This site, ANYONE
can join, it is FREE, you can showcase your work, network with others,
create projects with new friends, and of course showcase your sincere
dedicated hard work, promote yourselves, and promote your books,
movies, music, TV shows, radio shows, all your talent in the
Paranormal! Networking and helping others in a haunting or a Mufon
watch, the ideas are endless!

We are working hard to find sponsorships and unfortunately this 1st
annual event, donations are required to help offset the awards. Any
donations at $25.00 or more would be greatly appreciated.

All nominees, will become featured members. The donations are good
till Nov 7, 2009 and that&#39;s a wonderful savings and very affordable
for all to participate and enjoy ALL YOUR hard work!

Sending You All the Best from IPAA

http://www.ipaaward s.org &lt;http://www.ipaawards.org/&gt; 

Laura Kimberley,
Director of IPAA






